{
  "doc_id": "9267",
  "text": "GUS staining of roots inoculated with gusA tagged NGR234 was performed at 37 8C for 12-24 h according to Jefferson et al. [CITATION_1] . After staining, roots were rinsed in 100 mM potassium phosphate buffer, pH 7.0, and fixed for 4 h in a solution containing 2.5% (v/v) glutaraldehyde buffered with 200 mM sodium cacodylate, pH 7.2. Subsequently, the roots were rinsed in 100 mM potassium buffer and examined for bacterial colonization in whole specimens or in sections (30 mm thick sections cut with Microcut H1250, Energy Beam Sciences Inc., USA) with a Zeiss Axiophot II optical microscope using bright field optics (Carl Zeiss, Jena, Germany).",
